This paper is about geometric complexity theory, which is a subfield of computational complexity theory. The paper specifically focuses on the use of algebraic geometry and representation theory to approach the P vs. NP problem. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of integer programming, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also mentions the use of certain functions, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the relationship between the P vs. NP conjecture and the Riemann hypothesis over finite fields, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
